description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Medical Secretary in the Medical Secretariat, Business Support Division &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;15 hours – Monday and Friday - 8.30am until 4.30pm (Job Share) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide full secretarial support to a specific Consultant and his/her team within the Medical Secretariat, largely working on your own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will liaise with the other medical secretaries and colleagues in the team to ensure a smooth transference of information within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be well organised and used to dealing with the public, ensuring confidentiality, efficiency and politeness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to prioritise your own workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A sound knowledge of audio typing and medical terminology is desirable for the post. Experience of the Patient Centre system in accordance with Trust procedures. Assist in a timely way the co-ordination of care pathways (full training will be given).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work to a very high standard, as would be expected of a Senior Medical Secretary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous medical/hospital secretarial experience is essential for this post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this role fits your profile then we would love to have you as part of our team.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***PLEASE NOTE: When sufficient qualified applicants have been received this post will be closed***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alyson Lacey - Secretariat Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: sec.manager@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01553 214725&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katrina Miller - Secretariat Deputy Manager&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01553 613107&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: sec.manager@qehkl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
